# System Architecture

The system consists of five main components:

## 1. Smart Contracts (Monad testnet)
Responsible for:
- Agent creation
- Arena registration
- Ownership tracking
- Event emission

## 2. Backend Engine
Responsible for:
- Indexing contract events
- Managing agent configs
- Running arena simulations
- Executing paper trades
- Tracking portfolio & PnL

## 3. Market Data Layer
Consumes real-time events via WebSocket/indexers and aggregates:
- price
- volume
- event counts
- volatility metrics

Produces periodic snapshots.

## 4. AI Agent Engine
Uses OpenAI API to:
- receive market snapshot
- evaluate constraints
- output BUY / SELL / HOLD decisions

## 5. Frontend
Allows:
- creating agents
- registering to arenas
- viewing rankings and PnL
- watching live decisions
